# Six-Day Cycle

## The cycle

| Day | Focus |
|---|---|
| 1 | Ideate & Research |
| 2 | Design & Plan |
| 3-4 | Build |
| 5 | Test & Polish |
| 6 | Launch |
| Rest | Integrate, celebrate, prepare |

## Principles

- Rest is part of the work. Never 7-day weeks.
- Sustainable pace beats heroic sprints.
- Bounded work; intentional phase transitions.

## Scales

The pattern scales: 1-hour, 3-day, 6-day, 2-week cycles all work. Pick what fits the context.

## Anti-patterns

- Borrowing rest day "just this once"
- Stacking cycles without rest between
- Treating rest as "catch up on chores"
- All days as build days (no research, no polish)
